@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit System Context

' One box per service. Arrows show who talks to who.
' See the whole system before you zoom into any single hop.

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Browser" as browser

component "nginx\n(edge proxy, TLS)" as nginx
component "ui\n(React SPA, public)" as ui
component "auth\n(auth authority)" as auth
component "Redis\n(sessions)" as redis
component "node-gateway\n(event hub + WS)" as gw
component "python-worker\n(consumer)" as worker
queue "Kafka\njob.requests / orbit.public.jobs" as kafka
database "Postgres\n(jobs, owner)" as pg
component "Debezium\n(Kafka Connect)" as dbz

browser --> nginx : HTTPS + WebSocket\n(:80 -> 301 -> :443)
nginx --> ui : static SPA (public)
nginx --> auth : /api/login,logout,me + auth_request
nginx --> gw : /api/jobs (command), /api/jobs (history), /ws

auth --> redis : session:<id> (create / lookup + refresh TTL / delete)

gw --> pg : INSERT 'queued' (owner) ; SELECT history by owner
gw --> kafka : produce job.requests
kafka --> worker : consume job.requests
worker --> pg : UPDATE row -> 'completed'
pg --> dbz : WAL (logical replication)
dbz --> kafka : produce orbit.public.jobs
kafka --> gw : consume CDC
gw --> browser : job-update over WS

note bottom of nginx : The only public service and the only TLS endpoint.
note bottom of gw : Commands skip the auth service. The gateway is also the read model.
note bottom of kafka : You request work and report it through events.

@enduml
